{
  "texts": [
    "where α t is the probability attention score calculated from a softmax function, representing the importance of time t over the whole year.",
    "e t is the weight score of h t at time t calculated from a 4-layer feedforward neural network (FNN) with a Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU) as the activation function for the first three layers and a hyperbolic tangent function (tanh) for the last layer.",
    "W he,i and b he,i are the learnable weight and bias for the i th layer in the FNN, respectively (i = 1, 2, 3, and 4).",
    "α t and h t are then multiplied in the ATTN_Densor layer to calculate the annual yield:",
    "where y yield is the predicted yield for the input year, calculated from a 4-layer FNN with ReLU as the activation function for the first three layers."
  ]
}